OL,6,FBrendan Burke, prosecuting, had said
OL,7,Fin court: "He didn't see his children
OL,8,Ffor a few weeks simply because he
OL,9,Fdidn't want them to see their father
OL,10,Fin the state he was."
OL,12,FFollowing the first incident, Troy had
OL,13,Ftold police he was "smashed out of his
OL,14,Fhead" having attended a memorial
OL,15,Fservice for a friend earlier that day,
OL,16,Fand had "gone sick" by attacking the
OL,17,Fman.
OL,19,FWhile on bail for that offence, Troy
OL,20,Fthen went on to assault another male
OL,21,Fduring a separate second incident.
