OL,3,CTeenager jailed following two separate
OL,4,Cviolent attacks in town
OL,6,FThe court heard of Troy's childhood
OL,7,Fstruggles and mental health issues,
OL,8,Fthe death of a friend and his alcohol
OL,9,Fand substance misuse.
OL,11,FHis barrister, Kim Whittlestone, had
OL,12,Fsaid: "He knows he cannot go on like
OL,13,Fthis" and that "he is sorry for his
OL,14,Foffending."
OL,16,FJudge Michael Fanning acknowledged the
OL,17,Fchallenges faced by Troy, but said
OL,18,Fthat reports showed that Troy was an
OL,19,F"aggressive, unpredictable and, in
OL,20,Ffact, dangerous young man."
